                    ],
                    "index": 5,
                    "level": 1
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        171,
                        2330,
                        1188,
                        3061
                    ],
                    "type": "text",
                    "lines": [
                        {
                            "bbox": [
                                171,
                                2330,
                                1188,
                                3061
                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "By performing LFQPO phase- dependent spectral analysis, we found the most varied parameter between the energy spectra corresponding to the peak phase and the trough phase of the black hole LFQPOs, is the normalization norm in the Comptonization model we applied, and the second most varied parameter is the reflection fraction "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "\\mathcal{R}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": ". Both the Compton and reflection spectral components contribute to the LFQPOs observed in broadband X- rays. In the spectral model applied in our spectral analysis, the difference in the normalization norm represents the variation in the Compton emission component, and the parameter reflection fraction "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "\\mathcal{R}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " serves as an apparent amplification of the incident Compton component into the resulted reflection component, adding additional modulation in the reflection component with the LFQPO phase. Our investigation implies that the original timing signals or beats that are responsible for the LFQPOs lie in the Compton emission component, and the energy- dependent behavior of the LFQPOs at softer energies "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "(\\lesssim 30\\mathrm{keV})"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        171,
                                        2330,
                                        1188,
                                        3061
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " is the result of "
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "bbox": [
                                1267,
                                221,
                                2282,
                                404
                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1267,
                                        221,
                                        2282,
                                        404
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "the reflection component with a rather large reflection fraction. If the LFQPOs are due to Lense- Thirring precession, the phase information of precession then lies in the Compton component rather than in the reflection component."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
